# WHAT IT IS
#   `nsite` is the Nostr nip-34128 static-website protocol — a
#   way to host immutable web content (HTML, CSS, JS, images,
#   media) on the decentralized Nostr network instead of on a
#   centralized hosting provider.  The trick:
#
#     1. The site author uploads every file in a folder to one
#        or more **blossom servers** (the Nostr blob-storage
#        protocol — SHA-256 addressed BLOBs, BUD-01 through
#        BUD-08 + nip-94 file metadata).
#
#     2. For each uploaded file, the CLI publishes a Nostr
#        kind:34128 `website-content` event containing the
#        file's URL path (`d` tag), its blossom SHA-256 hash
#        (`x` tag), and the file's MIME type (`m` tag), signed
#        by the site author's Nostr `nsec`.
#
#     3. Any nsite-aware HTTP gateway (nsite.lol, npub.cash,
#        cloudfodder/nsite-ts gateways, the npub.pro CDN) can
#        then resolve `https://<npub>.<gateway>/<path>` by
#        querying Nostr for the corresponding kind:34128 event,
#        fetching the blob from a blossom server, and serving
#        it — censorship-resistant, no central hosting account,
#        no DNS, the npub IS the domain.
#
#   `nsite-cli` is the canonical reference uploader for this
#   protocol.  It diffs the local folder against the currently
#   published file list, uploads only the changed blobs to
#   the configured blossom servers, and publishes / updates
#   the corresponding kind:34128 events.
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from src/cli.ts + src/
#                       commands/{upload,ls,download}.ts
#                       commander.js subcommand registrations;
#                       extracted via raw.githubusercontent.com
#                       fetch of src/cli.ts and each command
#                       module)
#
#   nsite-cli <command> [args...] [options...]
#
#   Commands:
#     upload <folder>                Upload files from a directory
#         -f, --force                Force publishing even if no
#                                    changes were detected
#         -s, --servers <SERVERS>    Blossom servers to use
#                                    (comma separated)
#         -r, --relays <RELAYS>      Nostr relays to use
#                                    (comma separated)
#         -k, --privatekey <NSEC>    Private key (nsec/hex) to
#                                    sign with
#         -p, --purge                Delete online file events
#                                    that are not used anymore
#         -v, --verbose              Verbose output (file lists)
#         --publish-server-list      Publish the list of blossom
#                                    servers (Kind 10063)
#         --publish-relay-list       Publish the list of Nostr
#                                    relays (Kind 10002)
#         --publish-profile          Publish the npub profile
#                                    (Kind 0)
#         --fallback <FILE>          HTML file to copy and
#                                    publish as 404.html
#
#     ls [npub]                      List all files available
#                                    online for the npub (or for
#                                    the configured author if no
#                                    npub argument is given)
#         -r, --relays <RELAYS>      Nostr relays to use
#         -k, --privatekey <NSEC>    Private key (nsec/hex)
#
#     download <targetfolder> <npub>
#                                    Download all files available
#                                    online from the npub
#         -s, --servers <SERVERS>    Blossom servers to use
#         -r, --relays <RELAYS>      Nostr relays to use
#         -v, --verbose              Verbose output
#         -p, --purge                Delete extra local files
#
#   Standard commander.js auto-flags  (always available):
#     -h, --help                     Show help (top-level or
#                                    per-subcommand)
#     -V, --version                  Print version
#
# AXIS / CORPUS POSITION
